</div></div> </header><div class="grid-padding"><div class="col span8"><div id="ad-mpu-premium-1-narrow" class="ad-mpu-premium-1-narrow"><div class="ad ad--mpu-premium-1-narrow" id="ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_1_narrow-a2a4d3cdcd"><script type="text/javascript">Drupal.GPT.createSlot("ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_1_narrow-a2a4d3cdcd", function () {var m = Drupal.GPT.buildSizeMapping([[[0,0],[[300,250]]],[[480,0],[[300,250],[300,600]]],[[770,0],[]]]);var s = googletag.defineSlot(Drupal.GPT.unitPath(), m.define, "ad-manager-ad-mpu_premium_1_narrow-a2a4d3cdcd").defineSizeMapping(m.mapping.build()).setTargeting("pos", ["mpu_premium_1"]).addService(googletag.pubads());});</script></div></div><div id="recipetools" class="constantco-widget section-recipetools" data-app-resource-id="97547" data-type="recipetools" data-params="mobile_breakpoint=821"></div><div id="responsive-tabs" class="responsive-tabs responsive-tabs--2"><ul class="responsive-tabs__tabs"><li class="responsive-tabs__tab is-active"> <a href="#recipe-ingredients">Ingredients</a></li><li class="responsive-tabs__tab"> <a href="#recipe-method">Method</a></li></ul><div class="responsive-tabs__panes"> <section id="recipe-ingredients" class="responsive-tabs__pane is-active"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Ingredients</h2><div class="ingredients-list"><div class="ingredients-list__content"><ul class="ingredients-list__group"><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="about 4 skin-on chicken thighsand 4 drumsticks- buy a mixed pack">about 4 skin-on chicken thighs and 4 drumsticks- buy a mixed pack</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="6 tbsp piri-piri marinade(you can buy mild, medium or hot)">6 tbsp piri-piri marinade (you can buy mild, medium or hot)</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 tbsp sunflower oil">1 tbsp <a href="/glossary/sunflower-oil" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">sunflower oil</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary"><article id="node-260091" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/sunflower-oil"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/NEW-sunflower-oil%20IGNORE.jpg?itok=QlNpoo1a" width="100" height="100" alt="Sunflower oil" title="Sunflower oil" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/sunflower-oil">Sunflower oil</a></h2><p>A variety of oils can be used for baking. Sunflower is the one we use most often at Good Food as…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 peppers, any colour, deseeded and finely chopped">2 <a href="/glossary/pepper" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">peppers</a>, any colour, deseeded and finely chopped<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-253901" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/pepper"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/peppers.jpg?itok=Po5pM-we" width="100" height="100" alt="Peppers" title="Peppers come in variety of colours, and are related to chillies" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/pepper">Pepper</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">pep-iz</span><p>Also known as capsicums, bell peppers, sweet peppers or by their colours, for example red and…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="&#189; bunch spring onions, sliced, white and green parts separated">&#189; bunch <a href="/glossary/spring-onion" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">spring onions</a>, sliced, white and green parts separated<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-252336" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/spring-onion"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/springonions.jpg?itok=Vrl_tEXh" width="100" height="100" alt="Spring onions" title="Also known as scallions or green onions, spring onions are in fact very young onions, harvested before the bulb has had a chance to swell" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/spring-onion">Spring onion</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">sp-ring un-yun</span><p>Also known as scallions or green onions, spring onions are in fact very young onions, harvested…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="4 tbsp tomato purée">4 tbsp tomato purée</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 tbsp sweet smoked paprika">1 tbsp sweet smoked paprika</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="250g cooked rice">250g cooked <a href="/glossary/rice" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">rice</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-6030031" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/rice"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2016/08/rice.jpg?itok=s7RRNgFG" width="100" height="100" alt="Rice" title="Rice" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/rice">Rice</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">r-eye-s</span><p>Rice is a grain, the seed of a type of grass, which is the most widely grown and the most…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="vegetables or salad, to serve (optional)">vegetables or salad, to serve (optional)</li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6. Slash each piece of chicken 3 times, so the marinade can really flavour the meat. Pour over the sauce and leave in the fridge to marinate, if you have time. If not, mix well and arrange, skin-side up, in a roasting tin. Cook for 30 mins, then increase heat to 220C/200C fan/gas 7 and cook for about 15 mins more until the skin is crispy and golden.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>When the chicken is almost ready, heat the oil in a frying pan. Cook the peppers and white parts of the spring onions for 5 mins. Tip in the purée and paprika, stir, then add the rice, breaking up with a wooden spoon so all the grains are coated well. Use a high heat and scrape any that sticks off the bottom so you get some soft and some crispy parts. Heat until piping hot. Scatter the green parts of the spring onion on top and serve with the chicken, and some vegetables or salad, if you like.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food maga